Introduction

PIXY was a girl group under ALLART Entertainment and Happy Tribe Entertainment. They released their debut single "Wings" on February 24, 2021, as a six-member group: Ella, Lola, Satbyeol, Dia, Sua, and Dajeong.

Prior to their debut, member Ella was formerly known as a Cherry Bullet member under the stage name Mirae, while Satbyeol was previously a member of the girl group Girl's Alert, and Dajeong was a part of the kid girl group SUPA.

On August 27, 2022, ALLART Entertainment announced that Ella and Satbyeol had parted from the group for health and personal reasons. A month later, on September 27, 2022, they announced that they would be adding a new member, Rinji, to the group. She made her first promotion as part of the group with the start of their 1st European tour "Wanna Be Your Villian" on October 13, 2022.

On June 20, 2024, Dajeong announced via her Instagram that she had left PIXY.

On September 15, 2024, Lola announced on her Instagram that she had left the group and the agency.

On February 20, 2025, Rinji made her departure from the group after graduating from Hanlim Multi-Art School.

It is safe to assume that the group had quietly disbanded due to multiple departures and the their company's shut down.
